Bypass C99 restrict-in-array-bound on MSVC in lib/regex.h.

gnulib's regex.h declares regexec's __pmatch parameter as
  regmatch_t __pmatch[_Restrict_arr_ _REGEX_NELTS (__nmatch)]
which expands `_Restrict_arr_` to bare `restrict` on any compiler that
claims __STDC_VERSION__ >= 199901L.  MSVC under /std:c11 sets that
version macro but does not accept the restrict qualifier inside array
dimensions and errors out with C2143.

Force-include of a polyfill header via copts `/FI` did not survive
Bazel's MSVC toolchain translation reliably, so patch the source
directly: add an _MSC_VER branch that resolves `_Restrict_arr_` to
empty before the existing __STDC_VERSION__ check fires.  No-op on every
other compiler (the existing branches are unchanged, just promoted from
`# ifdef` to `# elif defined`).

--- a/lib/regex.h
+++ b/lib/regex.h
@@ -647,7 +647,12 @@
    Otherwise, GCC 3.1 and clang support this syntax (but not in C++ mode).
    Other ISO C99 compilers support it as well.  */
 #ifndef _Restrict_arr_
-# ifdef __restrict_arr
+# if defined _MSC_VER && !defined __clang__
+/* MSVC under /std:c11 advertises __STDC_VERSION__ >= 199901L but does
+   not accept `restrict` inside an array bound, so the original elif
+   chain below would expand `_Restrict_arr_` to `restrict` and fail.  */
+#  define _Restrict_arr_
+# elif defined __restrict_arr
 #  define _Restrict_arr_ __restrict_arr
 # else
 #  if ((199901L <= __STDC_VERSION__ \
